[{"question":"What steps should I take right now to set myself up for financial success?","answer":"Investments.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":4,"aSentId":5},{"question":"How do I start preparing for my retirement?","answer":"Suze Orman, dollars and cents, and the hottest issues of the day.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":12,"aSentId":13},{"question":"Ryan, why are you so opposed to gay people getting married?","answer":"A DEFENSE\": You know, I\u0027m not really opposed to anything in this situation.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":28,"aSentId":29},{"question":"Are you in favor of gay marriage?","answer":"I\u0027m in favor of having the citizens have the authority to go to the ballot box and vote about marriage.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":37,"aSentId":38},{"question":"Are you in favor or against gay marriage?","answer":"I\u0027m in favor of marriage between a man and a woman.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":48,"aSentId":49},{"question":"That basically the reason a man and a woman should be allowed to marry rather than a man and a man or a woman and a woman, is to do with their ability to procreate?","answer":"I don\u0027t think it\u0027s only that.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":58,"aSentId":59},{"question":"Is that part of it?","answer":"That\u0027s part of it.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":61,"aSentId":62},{"question":"So would you ban everyone over the age of 50 from getting married?","answer":"No.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":65,"aSentId":66},{"question":"Is your answer to that question yes?","answer":"The Supreme Court looked at these cases of the fundamental right to marry for prisoners and they understood again because of what marriage is, is a union of a man and a woman, prisoners have that same right partly because they come out of jail and they still have lives.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":91,"aSentId":92},{"question":"What it boils down to?","answer":"I feel compassion for you, and I\u0027ll tell you why.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":135,"aSentId":136},{"question":"Where does the American Constitution say that a same-sex couple can\u0027t get married?","answer":"The Constitution doesn\u0027t, which is why the Supreme Court shouldn\u0027t say that.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":161,"aSentId":162},{"question":"Do -- is that what you think is going to happen?","answer":"But don\u0027t want to have to obscure -- I think these are secondary issues.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":224,"aSentId":225},{"question":"Why?","answer":"So how do we strengthen the message that they shouldn\u0027t get divorced.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":231,"aSentId":232},{"question":"What if you were sterile and you couldn\u0027t have a child?","answer":"And marriage is what connects the mother and the father with each other for the child.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":252,"aSentId":253},{"question":"Really?","answer":"-- we can have the government out of the marriage system.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":260,"aSentId":261},{"question":"Really?","answer":"We\u0027re in the court of this public opinion, but in America, there are lots of people who agree with me.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":266,"aSentId":267},{"question":"How old are you?","answer":"I\u0027m 31.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":272,"aSentId":273},{"question":"Is it more of them than us?","answer":"It\u0027s -- I think at this point it is more of them than us, if you define us as main street, the people possibly in this room.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":318,"aSentId":319},{"question":"So what\u0027s the interest rate of your student loans?","answer":"I\u0027m going to act like that\u0027s rhetorical because I don\u0027t know.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":342,"aSentId":343},{"question":"Suze, what would you recommend?","answer":"Well, now here we have the argument --","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":376,"aSentId":377},{"question":"OK?","answer":"Arguments over marriage.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":379,"aSentId":380},{"question":"Is she?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":390,"aSentId":391},{"question":"So that\u0027s why -- because -- do you feel -- and do you feel like you\u0027re OK?","answer":"Yes, I do.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":392,"aSentId":393},{"question":"Really?","answer":"OK.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":403,"aSentId":404},{"question":"So do you have more than one piece of real estate?","answer":"Yes, I do.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":425,"aSentId":426},{"question":"How many do you have?","answer":"Two, going to be three.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":427,"aSentId":428},{"question":"Are they really complicated, your taxes?","answer":"On and off.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":430,"aSentId":431},{"question":"Fundamentally, is it getting older or younger now, the retirement age of most Americans?","answer":"Years ago, I used to sit and I used to say to everybody, take Social Security at 62.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":476,"aSentId":477},{"question":"You have piece for Tiger Woods?","answer":"I love this for him.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":499,"aSentId":500},{"question":"What do you make of that as a marketing ploy?","answer":"I think that was a very, very large mistake.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":511,"aSentId":512},{"question":"How do you recover from it?","answer":"Here\u0027s what you understand, if there was ever a time to go through bankruptcy, it is now.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":530,"aSentId":531},{"question":"What do you think about Cheryl Sandberg\u0027s new book \"Lean In\"?","answer":"Love it.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":548,"aSentId":549},{"question":"But if it\u0027s a woman producer and she leaves your hotel room at 3:00 or 4:00 in the morning, what\u0027s everybody going to think?","answer":"Hard working girl.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":572,"aSentId":573},{"question":"Another glass ceiling gets chipped away?","answer":"I love that.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":589,"aSentId":590},{"question":"Do you want to get married, by the way?","answer":"Oh, so badly here, I can\u0027t even tell you.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":617,"aSentId":618},{"question":"And how would you suggest going about that?","answer":"Well, you have to first teach them where are they going to get this money that they\u0027re going to save.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":639,"aSentId":640},{"question":"Why are you giving them an allowance?","answer":"Well, they have to earn it.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":643,"aSentId":644},{"question":"Are you saving money for you?","answer":"I am trying.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":658,"aSentId":659},{"question":"Do Americans overspend?","answer":"Yes, Americans overspend.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":677,"aSentId":678},{"question":"If I could get you to leave us with one overriding thought for all Americans tonight to think about money in a sensible way, what would you want it to be?","answer":"That, you know, just seriously to live below your means but within your needs.","docId":"130326pmt","qSentId":699,"aSentId":700}]